Two women have been attacked by two Pitbull s at the Bluff in KwaZulu-Natal, while walking on the beach in Sloane Road on Friday.The incident took place early in the morning and Paramedics were called onto the scene just after 09:15. Paramedics found two females and a dog which is also believed to have been attacked by the Pitbull s. Pit Bulls attacked the people whilst they were walking on the beach. Both females had sustained moderate bites to their lower limbs and were stabilised on the scene by Advanced Life Support Paramedics before being transported to a nearby hospital for the further care that they required, Arrive Alive said.Arrive Allive said one of the injured dogs was transported to the vet and that the other one ran away after the attack.Meanwhile, Police will be investigating the incident further.-TNA Reporter